TITLE: US says Russia isn't serious about allowing Ukraine grain exports
SUMMARY: Russian officials are not operating in good faith in negotiations with the U.N. over allowing Ukraine to make grain exports through the Black Sea, U.S. officials say.

TITLE: US, South Korea conduct joint navy drills ahead of possible North Korea nuclear test
SUMMARY: Officials in the U.S. and the Indo-Pacific region have warned that North Korea is set to conduct its first nuclear test after satellite images showed construction at a facility.

TITLE: Boris Johnson faces 'no confidence' vote after polls show he would lose election held today: Report
SUMMARY: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson would lose parliament as well as his own seat as a minister if the government held an election, new polling data showed.

TITLE: Queen’s Platinum Jubilee wraps up with London street pageant
SUMMARY: Queen Elizabeth II's Platinum Jubilee celebrating her 70 years on the throne will come to an end in London on Sunday, capping off with a colorful street pageant.

TITLE: Syrian army should use air defenses against Turkish invasion, US-backed SDF says
SUMMARY: The U.S.-backed Syrian Democratic Forces commander said Sunday that Syria should use its air defense system against Turkish planes if an invasion were to take place.

TITLE: Pope Francis fuels new speculation on future of pontificate
SUMMARY: Pope Francis adds fuel to the rumor he will eventually take the same steps as his predecessor to step down after announcing a visit to Italy's L’Aquila.

TITLE: International food crisis stemming from Ukraine war has no quick fixes, experts say
SUMMARY: The looming international food shortage, exasperated by the Ukraine war, doesn't have any quick solutions and could leave millions without food, experts say.

TITLE: Russian missiles strike Kyiv for first time in a month, targeting tank facility
SUMMARY: A Russian missile strike on Kyiv targeted a facility housing foreign-supplied tanks and armored vehicles Sunday, shattering the city's sense of relative calm.

TITLE: Japan's increased defense budget make a difference in China deterrence, 'no serious discussion' on nukes
SUMMARY: Japan's pledge to double the spending on its military budget would see the country jump from the ninth-largest to the third-largest budget in the world behind the U.S. and China.

TITLE: Putin says Russia will hit harder if US supplies long-range missiles to Ukraine
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin warned the West that Russia would strike new targets if the U.S. began supplying Ukraine with longer-range missiles.

TITLE: Kyiv hit by explosions as war continues in eastern Ukraine
SUMMARY: Ukraine's capital city was struck by several explosions early Sunday, a day after officials said its troops had recaptured part of the city of Sievierodonetsk.

TITLE: North Korea fires volley of missiles after US, South Korea stage drills
SUMMARY: North Korea fired eight short-range ballistic missiles towards the sea off its east coast on Sunday, a day after South Korea and the United States finished with combined military exercises.

TITLE: Tiananmen Square: Taiwan vigil remembers victims of China massacre
SUMMARY: Taiwan took the place of Hong Kong by hosting a commemoration for the victims of the Tiananmen Square massacre. Before the 2020 violent crackdown against pro-democracy activists, Hong Kong held events to remember the victims of the anti-government protests.

TITLE: Historic Ukrainian monastery burns after Russian shelling, Zelenskyy says
SUMMARY: Russian artillery sets fire to a historic church and monastery in Ukraine.

TITLE: Ukraine feels no pressure from allies on peace talks with Russia: ambassador
SUMMARY: Henry Kissinger recently suggested that Ukraine will have to concede territories it had lost prior to Russia's invasion as part of peace talks and appeasement with Moscow.

TITLE: London's Trafalgar Square evacuated due to suspicious vehicle, police conduct 'controlled explosion': report
SUMMARY: Authorities responded to a suspicious vehicle in London's Trafalgar Square on Saturday.

TITLE: Ukraine claims it has taken back part of eastern city of Sievierodonetsk from Russia
SUMMARY: Ukraine said Friday it had reclaimed a portion of the city of Sievierodonetsk that it had lost to Russia and that it could control it for up to two weeks.

TITLE: The fight for rare Earth minerals
SUMMARY: Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin will meet with his Chinese counterpart, Defense Minister Wei Fenghe face to face for the first time in a tour of Asia next week. The Chinese government formally reached out to the Pentagon Friday to set up the meeting.

TITLE: Reporter's Notebook: Russian activist says Ukraine war opposition efforts alive, but fraught with risk
SUMMARY: Sergei Ukhov, who operates a Telegram channel following Russia's war in Ukraine, says the anti-war movement is alive and well in Perm, the gateway to Siberia.

TITLE: Turkey NATO veto drives Swedish culture clash around Kurdish minister
SUMMARY: Amineh Kakabaveh served as a time as a member of the Peshmerga Kurdish group, which has complicated Sweden's NATO bid as Turkey seeks anti-Kurdish assurances.
